Gaston's Sandwich: The ham-sandwich looks fresh and nutritious in you hand, begging to be eaten.
You: "Friends forever!" (Eat your half of the sandwich.)
Kim Kitsuragi: "Sure, sure." The lieutenant nods impatiently. "Time to go solve a murder investigation."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I'll pass," the lieutenant replies with a polite nod. "Thanks."
Authority: When you hold something up long enough, some people are compelled to take it. Try it on the lieutenant.
Gaston's Sandwich: You really ram into the sandwich, *deep*. The tomato slides off, mayo drips everywhere (including your moustache and clothes), bits of ham fall onto the ground...
Gaston's Sandwich: You can barely feel the taste, but it seems decent enough. At least it gets your stomach nice and full. Good sandwich -- durable!
You: "Congratulations, Kim. It was a test and you passed."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Officer. We have serious matters to attend to. I suggest we get to them right now." He seems completely unfazed by the situation.
You: "What do you mean 'you'll pass'?"
"Why won't you take the sandwich?"
Kim Kitsuragi: He shrugs. "I mean I'm not hungry and therefore am not gonna take it. Thanks though."
"I'm just not hungry and therefore have little reason to take it."
You: Proceed with the mission.
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant slaps the sandwich out of your hand faster than you could ever hope to react in your sorry state. It lands in the dirt and falls apart.
You: "Yes! By sharing this sandwich you and I solidify the bond between us."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Is it really necessary?"
You: "I just thought it would be a nice gesture. I'm sorry..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "No, it's... it's okay. Let's share it, okay?" The lieutenant breaks the sandwich in two and quickly eats his half.
Esprit de Corps: This man does not crack under pressure. Stars would die before he'd succumb to any kind of manipulation. With this realization comes a sudden flash of pride.
You: Lower the sandwich.
You: Have the sandwich-interceptor circle in front of the lieutenant's face and then gently nosedive against his lips.
You: "You know, Kim, if I were to hold this sandwich up long enough..."
